    "body": "### Problem\n\nFor a verilog file (named 'test.v') which has a module definition with syntax error, for example:\n```\nmodule test (\n    input a,\n    output b\n);\n\nassign b = a\n\nendmodule\n```\n\nThe error will report twice:\n\n<img width=\"1276\" height=\"269\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/32aea6ad-8247-4476-aa19-1f69d943536e\" />\n\nI expect that the error message should only report once.\nI use Lazyvim, and use verible as verilog LSP, as following:\n\n<img width=\"1309\" height=\"613\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ac4a75cb-96bb-4698-b5e3-dde546859a6f\" />\n\nI have tried steps to repoduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\", but the code template has error, and LSP is not started after I correct the error.\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\nthe code template has syntax error, and I cannot use it to reproduce the bug.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI expect that the error message should only report once.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev\n\n### Language server name/version\n\nverible-verilog-ls/v0.0-4051-g9fdb4057\n\n### Operating system/version\n\ncentos7\n\n### Log file\n\n_No response_",
